name: Air Fryer Oven Taco Shells
author: Yoly
summary: I do not care for the premade taco shells sold at the supermarket. So I developed this recipe in my Cuisinart® Air Fryer Oven. These taco shells are crispy, golden brown, and ready to be stuffed with your favorite fillings. The best part is they are oil free and greaseless.
ingredients: 4 (4 inch) street taco corn tortillas (such as Mission®)
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Place a mini muffin tin pan upside down the air fryer basket
Position tortillas in the indents of the muffin tin
Place the basket on the lowest rack of the air fryer oven
Air fry until golden brown and crispy, about 3 minutes
Remove tortillas from mini muffin tin pan and place upside down in the basket
Air fry until bottom side is crispy and golden brown, 1 minute more
